doc.previous: Six subspecies are currently recognised characterised principally by differences in size and plumage There is a steady change to the birds morphology and size the further south they are encountered with lighter and more greyish plumage larger body size and a shorter bill Southerly populations also show more white plumage in the tail with less whiteness on the wing 7
